text:
Ingemar Skogö (4 January 1949 – 28 May 2019) was a Swedish civil servant. Skogö was a graduate of Lund University. He served as the Governor of Västmanland County from 2009 to 2015. Skogö was also the Director-General of the Civil Aviation Administration from 1992 to 2001, and the Swedish Road Administration from 2001 to 2009.
Skogö was born in Tranås. He died on 28 May 2019, at the age of 70.
